JOHANNESBURG - The Road Traffic Management Corporation's launched an urgent court application against private company Tasima over the e-Natis system. It wants to force Tasima to hand over the system following a Constitutional Court order.The handover was meant to have been done 30 days after the November ruling.READ: eNatis to be handed over to the Transport DepartmentTasima s managed the e-Natis system since 2001.Its contract was unlawfully extended in 2009, prompting the legal action by RTMC and the transport department.eNatis is the official register for all vehicles driving licences and traffic infringements.The application will be heard at the North Gauteng High Court in Pretoria on Friday.eNCA